-- Israel Draws With Azerbaijan 1-1 in European World Cup Qualifier
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-09-07T19:56:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-07/israel-draws-with-azerbaijan-1-1-in-european-world-cup-qualifier.html
Israel came from behind to draw 1-1
with Azerbaijan and stay in the running for a berth in the 2014
soccer  World Cup .  Itay Schechter scored in the 73rd minute for Israel at
Winter Stadium in  Ramat Gan . Rahid Amirguliyev had given visting
Azerbaijan the lead 12 minutes earlier.  The draw keeps Israel in third place in European Group F
with 12 points with three qualifiers remaining. Portugal leads
with 17 points, two more than Russia, which hosts Israel in
three days.  The winners of the nine European groups qualifies for the
World Cup in Brazil, with the best eight runners-up going into a
playoff for the remaining four slots.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  